{"title":"In the Drops: Ineos Grenadiers’ Gobik bib shorts, super-fast Trek bottles, a gravel rides handbook and Hiplok’s nifty zip tie","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/gobik-lancer-bib-shorts","date":1740134573000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/gobik-lancer-bib-shorts\">In the Drops: Ineos Grenadiers’ Gobik bib shorts, super-fast Trek bottles, a gravel rides handbook and Hiplok’s nifty zip tie </a></p>\n\n<p>Just as the bike world is looking to rouse itself from its winter hibernation proper – the WorldTour season has properly kicked off, and my inbox is filling up with product launches happening in the near future – Geraint Thomas goes and drops the bombshell that he’s retiring this year.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>OK, it’s no huge surprise, but it’s still sad to see one of Britain’s best ever riders leave the racing side of the sport. Ewan Wilson actually kicked off the week by posing the question of whether he <em>was</em> in fact the best rider we’ve produced, and <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/geraint-thomas-best-team-sky\">he makes a compelling case for an answer in the affirmative</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The refresh of our Game Changer feature series is getting to the business end. We followed up last week’s ones with the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/game-changer-bell-biker-helmet\">Bell Biker helmet</a>, <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/game-changer-campagnolo-gran-sport-derailleur\">Campagnolo’s Gran Sport derailleur</a>, the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/game-changer-cervelo-soloist\">Cervélo Soloist</a> and <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/cycling-game-changer-look-clipless-pedals\">Look’s clipless pedals</a>. Look out for our article on the other tech that has got cycling to where it is today being published early next week.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Aside from important products we also brushed up some facts and figures, namely talking about <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/what-is-bicycle-head-angle\">a bike’s head angle</a>, asking <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/how-does-frame-geometry-affect-a-bike\">how geometry affects a bike</a> and <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/bicycle-gear-ratios-explained\">explaining how gear ratios work</a>, before topping it off with our latest <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/phil-burt-bike-fit-podcast\">podcast with bike-fit guru, Phil Burt</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>As ever with <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/in-the-drops\">In the Drops</a>, it’s a case of come for the content, stay for the kit, so without further ado, here is a selection of new stuff you should know about.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n<h2>Gobik Lancer bib shorts</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-7-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Black Gobik Lancer bibshorts\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-7-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-7-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-7-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-7-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-7-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-7-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-7-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-7-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-7-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-7.jpg 2000w\" /><figcaption>Sam Challis</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>With the nights starting to get shorter and (hopefully) the worst of the cold weather behind us, our thoughts can start to turn to this year’s fancy summer kit. It doesn’t look to get fancier than <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/gobik-insider\">Gobik’s</a> new Lancer bib shorts, which the brand says has been developed in partnership with one of its sponsored pro teams, Ineos Grenadiers, who have been racing in versions of the design for most of last season.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Given a hefty price and pro input, Gobik promises the Lancers offer the best of all worlds: while they are pretty lightweight and breathable, Gobik says thanks to minimal seams and a compressive fabric that extends lower than regular shorts, they also offer aerodynamic properties.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-9-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Black Gobik Lancer bibshorts\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-9-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-9-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-9-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-9-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-9-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-9-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-9-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-9-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-9-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-9.jpg 2000w\" /><figcaption>Sam Challis</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The ‘K12’ chamois has been made for Gobik by specialists <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/elastic-interface-factory-visit\">Elastic Interface</a> and contains that enigmatic substance graphene, which Gobik says offers better thermoregulation and antibacterial attributes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Lazer cut panels, thermosealed hems and canny silicone dot grippers at the ends of the shorts aiming to create second skin-like fit to finish things off.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>To find out more about the Gobik Lancer bibshorts, visit <a href=\"https://gobik.com/en/products/bib-short-lancer-men-black-k12\" target=\"_blank\">gobik.com (€190)</a></strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/subscriptions?utm_source=Web&amp;utm_medium=Banner&amp;utm_campaign=Banner+1\"><img width=\"970\" height=\"300\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/Subs-flash-161-for-web-1-970x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/Subs-flash-161-for-web-1-970x300.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/Subs-flash-161-for-web-1-300x93.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/Subs-flash-161-for-web-1-768x238.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/Subs-flash-161-for-web-1-1536x476.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/Subs-flash-161-for-web-1-2048x634.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/Subs-flash-161-for-web-1-750x232.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/Subs-flash-161-for-web-1-1140x353.jpg 1140w\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Trek RSL Aero bottles and cages</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-11-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Trek water bottles and white bottle cages\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-11-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-11-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-11-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-11-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-11-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-11-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-11-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-11-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-11-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-11.jpg 2000w\" /><figcaption>Sam Challis</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>At £90 per bottle and cage, Trek’s new RSL Aero setup won’t be considered by most as top priority as far as cost-effective <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/best-road-bike-upgrades\">upgrades</a> go. However, this might be a price worth paying for those looking for extra free speed, as Trek says they will make any bike faster.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>‘We can’t give exact figures as it’s dependent on the individual bike, but the system was launched with the <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/reviews/trek-madone-gen-8-road-bike-review\">Madone Gen 8</a> and imparts a 1.8 watt advantage at 35kmh on that bike,’ says John Davis, the Madone’s lead aerodynamicist.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-13-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Trek white bottle cages\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-13-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-13-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-13-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-13-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-13-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-13-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-13-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-13-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-13-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-13.jpg 2000w\" /><figcaption>Sam Challis</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The bottles help fair the bike’s main triangle, smoothing airflow across that area to achieve the advantage. While these aero gains depend on the RSL bottles being in place to work, thankfully the cages fit regular bottles as well, so practicality hasn’t been totally sacrificed for performance.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>To find out more about the Trek RSL Aero bottles and cages, visit <a href=\"https://www.trekbikes.com/gb/en_GB/equipment/bike-accessories/bike-water-bottles-cages/bike-water-bottles/trek-rsl-aero-water-bottle-and-cage/p/46175/\" target=\"_blank\">trekbikes.com (£89.99)</a></strong></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/bmc-kaius-01-recall\">BMC issues safety recall for Kaius 01 gravel bike </a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/buying-guides/free-to-air-cycling\">Which countries can watch cycling for free in 2025</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/phil-burt-bike-fit-podcast\">Cyclist Magazine Podcast: Phil Burt, the king of bike fit</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/all-you-need-to-know-about-the-classics-monuments-cobbles\">Cycling Spring Classics 2025: Race dates, Monuments, cobbles and live TV guide</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2><em>Gravel Rides South West England</em> by Katherine Moore</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-1-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Gravel rides route book\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-1-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-1-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-1-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-1-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-1-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-1-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-1-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-1-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-1.jpg 2000w\" /><figcaption>Sam Challis</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Full disclosure: <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/author/katherine-moore\">Katherine</a> is a regular contributor to <em>Cyclist</em> and I live in the South West, so I’m never not going to be able to consider this book dispassionately. Even so, if you’re after a comprehensive guide to the myriad tracks and trails in the West Country and beyond, I think you’d be hard pressed to find a better resource.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Produced by Vertebrate Publishing, which offers cycling guidebooks for a number of other areas in the UK, Gravel Rides South West includes 24 routes, ranging from 16km pootles to 180km epics. Between them, they aim to show off the best the South West has to offer off-road.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-2-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Gravel rides route book\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-2-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-2-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-2-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-2-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-2-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-2-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-2-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-2-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-2.jpg 2000w\" /><figcaption>Sam Challis</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>As a local, it’s nice to see some popular routes given the exposure they deserve, but it’s equally great to learn more about rides basically on my doorstep that I had no idea about before rifling through Katherine’s book. It’s comprehensively written, beautifully shot and worth a read if you’re looking to explore the area on a gravel bike.</p>\n\n\n\n<div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<h2>Hiplok Z-Lok Combo</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-4-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Orange Hiplok zip tie lock\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-4-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-4-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-4-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-4-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-4-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-4-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-4-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-4-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-4-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-4.jpg 2000w\" /><figcaption>Sam Challis</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Hiplok’s Z-Lok Combo is essentially what would result if you gave ChatGPT repeated prompts to design the humble zip-tie’s ultimate form: make it zippier, make it tie-ier, etc.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Z-Lok is a reusable zip-tie in concept but made from plastic coated steel, using a built-in three-digit combination lock to secure it. It’s small enough to fit in a back pocket (though also comes with a mount so it can be fixed in place of a bottle cage), but it’s long enough to secure a frame tube to most poles/railings etc.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-6-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"Orange Hiplok zip tie lock\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-6-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-6-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-6-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-6-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-6-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-6-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-6-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-6-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-6-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/in-the-drops-21-02-25-6.jpg 2000w\" /><figcaption>Sam Challis</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It won’t stand up to the concerted attack of a grinder, but equally, that isn’t what it’s designed for. What it is good at is dissuading opportunist thieves from simply walking off with a bike.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It should be an ideal product to bring along if you’re seeking extra peace of mind at a cafe stop, if you’re more like me, the pub.</p>\n\n\n\n<div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div><div>\n<p><em><strong>Ad feature</strong></em></p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Discover magical Slovenia with SloVelo Escapes</h2>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/slovelo-solus-01.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/slovelo-solus-01.jpg 1200w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/slovelo-solus-01-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/slovelo-solus-01-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/slovelo-solus-01-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/slovelo-solus-01-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/slovelo-solus-01-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/slovelo-solus-01-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/slovelo-solus-01-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/slovelo-solus-01-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p><strong>SloVelo Escapes offers unforgettable cycling adventures in the heart of Slovenia, Europe’s latest cycling heaven…</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Taking you through the breathtaking landscapes of this outdoor gem, our escapes are designed for passionate riders who seek more than just a bike trip – they’re about creating lifelong memories, connecting with like-minded people, and immersing yourself in the rich local culture.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Two extraordinary cycling getaways in 2025…</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Both of SloVelo’s 2025 tours are tailored for intermediate cyclists looking to challenge themselves while enjoying an all-inclusive experience. Every ride is carefully designed to showcase Slovenia’s diverse terrain, from its sun-kissed coastline to its towering Alpine peaks.</p>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"600\" height=\"400\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/slovelo-solus-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/slovelo-solus-1.jpg 600w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/slovelo-solus-1-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/slovelo-solus-1-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/slovelo-solus-1-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p><strong>Slovenian Coast Escape (2nd-6th May)</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>• Ride along Slovenia’s stunning Adriatic coastline, where the sea breeze meets picturesque vineyards and charming medieval towns.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>• Indulge in the finest local delicacies and wines, with routes that blend scenic beauty with cultural discovery.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>• Ideal for riders who love rolling hills, coastal views and a mix of adventure and relaxation.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>•<strong> Prices:</strong> £1,050 per person (shared accommodation) / £1,400 (single occupancy).</p>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"600\" height=\"400\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/slovelo-solus-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/slovelo-solus-2.jpg 600w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/slovelo-solus-2-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/slovelo-solus-2-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/slovelo-solus-2-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p><strong>Julian Alps Escape (2nd-8th June)</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>• Conquer Slovenia’s legendary mountain passes and soak in breathtaking Alpine landscapes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>• Ride through serene meadows, alongside crystal-clear lakes, and over challenging climbs that reward you with awe-inspiring views.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>• Experience <strong>Slovenia’s ‘Queen Stage’</strong>, featuring the iconic <strong>Vršič Pass (1,611m)</strong> and the spectacular <strong>Mangart Saddle Road (2,055m)</strong> – Slovenia’s highest road, offering an unforgettable test of endurance with unmatched panoramas.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>• A true escape for those who crave adventure, endurance, and the thrill of high-altitude cycling.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>• Prices: £1,400 per person (shared accommodation) / £1,750 (single occupancy).</p>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"665\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/slovelo-solus-02-970x665.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/slovelo-solus-02-970x665.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/slovelo-solus-02-300x206.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/slovelo-solus-02-768x527.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/slovelo-solus-02-750x514.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/slovelo-solus-02-1140x782.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/02/slovelo-solus-02.jpg 1200w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p><strong>We take care of everything so you can focus on the ride. </strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/14.0.0/72x72/2714.png\" alt=\"✔\" /> <strong>Expertly guided routes</strong> tailored to challenge and inspire.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/14.0.0/72x72/2714.png\" alt=\"✔\" /> <strong>Gourmet dining experiences</strong> prepared by private chef Robert Dežutelj.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/14.0.0/72x72/2714.png\" alt=\"✔\" /> <strong>Daily yoga sessions</strong> to keep your body strong and flexible.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/14.0.0/72x72/2714.png\" alt=\"✔\" /> <strong>Luxury accommodations</strong> in hand-picked locations that offer both comfort and charm.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/14.0.0/72x72/2714.png\" alt=\"✔\" /> <strong>Transport from airports:</strong> We’ll arrange convenient transfers from the airport to the start of the tour, ensuring a seamless journey from the moment you arrive.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>These exclusive cycling getaways have <strong>limited availability</strong>, with only a handful of spots remaining. <strong>Secure your place now</strong> and get ready for an unforgettable adventure in the spectacular surroundings of Slovenia.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Slo Up, Velo Down!</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<div>\n<div><a href=\"https://www.sloveloescapes.com/?deliveryName=FCP_1_DM312054\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Book your escape now!</strong></a></div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div></div>\n\n\n\n<p><em><strong>Ad feature ends</strong></em></p>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/newsletters\"><img width=\"970\" height=\"351\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-970x351.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-970x351.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-300x109.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-768x278.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-1536x556.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-2048x741.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-750x271.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-1-1140x412.jpg 1140w\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/gobik-lancer-bib-shorts\">In the Drops: Ineos Grenadiers’ Gobik bib shorts, super-fast Trek bottles, a gravel rides handbook and Hiplok’s nifty zip tie </a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Sam Challis &#124; Tech Editor","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a3